    "recap_headline": "University of Northern Colorado Athletics",
    "recap_text": "FAYETTEVILLE, Ark\n. -\u00a0Northern Colorado baseball mounted a late-inning rally, but it wasn't enough to erase an early deficit in a 9\u20134 loss to No. four Arkansas in Wednesday's midweek finale.\nArkansas set the tone early, pushing across three runs in the first three innings and consistently applying pressure at the plate. The Razorbacks added to their lead with a two-run fourth and later broke the game open in the seventh, finishing with nine runs on 11 hits.\nThe Bears were held quiet through the first six innings, managing just one hit against Arkansas starter Peyton Lee, who struck out six over five scoreless frames. Northern Colorado broke through late, scoring four runs in the eighth inning to cut into the deficit.\nBrandon Sanchez\nprovided the big swing with a two-run home run, finishing 1-for-2 with two RBIs and two walks.\nSam Pease\nadded a two-run hit of his own, going 1-for-3 with two RBIs.\nBrien Kenny\n,\nEthan Mooser\nand\nEaston Bryant\neach recorded a hit as the Bears totaled five on the day.\nOn the mound,\nLogan Moser\ntook the loss after allowing three runs over 2.1 innings. UNC cycled through several pitchers, including\nLucas Stone\nand\nMason Bright\n, but couldn't slow Arkansas offense to close the gap.\nON DECK:\nNorthern Colorado continues its road swing with a trip to Omaha to resume Summit League play against the Omaha Mavericks. The three-game conference series is set to begin on Friday, March 20.\nDIAMOND CLUB\nThe Diamond Club plays a vital role in supporting the UNC Baseball program. By giving to the Diamond Club, you help provide access to facility enhancements\u2014such as the Jackson Field Turf Project\u2014along with advanced technology and elevated daily operations, giving our student-athletes the resources to compete and excel at the highest level.\nGive to the Diamond Club today!\nFOLLOW THE BEARS\nFor complete coverage of UNC Athletics, visit uncbears.com. Follow the baseball team on X (formerly Twitter) (@UNC_BearsBSB) and Instagram (@UNC_BearsBaseball)."
